               <p>HENRY HEATH. I am an apprentice to Mr. Bowden, he is a <rs id="t18160710-94-viclabel500" type="occupation">hatter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160710-94-victim681 t18160710-94-viclabel500"></join>, at 166, Shoreduch. I lost a hat on the 21st of June, at about half past nine in the evening; it was about a foot within the shop door on a stand.</p>

               <p>WILLIAM BARRETT. I saw the prisoner and another on the evening of the day in the indictment; they made several attempts at several shops, and at last, I saw the prisoner take this hat. I pursued him; he dropped the hat, and I secured him.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160710-94-person682">
                  GEORGE 
                  WOODROFFE
               <interp inst="t18160710-94-person682" type="surname" value="WOODROFFE"></interp>
